article.description: Utah Valley St. 66, S. Dakota St. 54
article.headline: Utah Valley St. 66, S. Dakota St. 54
article.linkText: Utah Valley St. 66, S. Dakota St. 54
article.story: BROOKINGS, S.D. (AP) -- Utah Valley State pulled away in the second half to beat South Dakota State 66-54 on Thursday, handing the Jackrabbits their fifth straight loss. Utah Valley State (13-6) took a one-point lead into the half, but stretched the lead to double digits midway through the second half. Joran Brady and Ryan Toolson scored 17 points each for the Wolverines. Brady had a game-high 13 rebounds. Peter Brown added 10 points. South Dakota State (4-15) has lost eight of its last 10 games. With the game still up for grabs with just over five minutes to play, SDSU went three minutes without scoring a point. The Jackrabbits struggled from the field, hitting just 32 percent. They also were 0-for-13 from 3-point range. The Wolverines made five of their 11 3-pointers in the first half and went 8-for-17 for the game. Utah Valley State took its first 12-point lead of the second half at 58-46 on a jumper by Brady with 5:15 to play in the game. SDSU trailed 58-50 with 4:07 to play, but the Jackrabbits went scoreless for the next three minutes. They got no closer than seven points the rest of the way. Michael Loney led the Jackrabbits with 14 points. Matt Cadwell added 11 and Kai Williams 10.
